{META_DATA}: THE SOCIAL NETWORK
{META_DATA}: Written by
{META_DATA}: Aaron Sorkin
{META_DATA}: May 28, 2009
{META_DATA}: FROM THE BLACK WE HEAR--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Did you know there are more people with genius IQ's living in China than there are people of any kind living in the United States?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ERICA (V.O. )
{DIALOGUE}: That can't be true.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: it is true.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ERICA (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What would account for that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK (V.0.)
{DIALOGUE}: Well first of all, a lot of people live in China.
{DIALOGUE}: But here's my question:
{META_DATA}: FADE IN
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAMPUS BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MARK ZUCKERBERG is a sweet looking 19 year old whose lack of any physically intimidating attributes masks a very complicated and dangerous anger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has trouble making eye contact- and sometimes it's hard to tell if he's talking to you or to himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ERICA, also 19, is Mark's date.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has a girl-next-door face that makes her easy to fall for.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At this point in the conversation she already knows that she'd rather not be there and her politeness is about to be tested.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The scene is stark and simple.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK
{DIALOGUE}: How do you distinguish yourself in a population of people who all got 1600 on their SAT's?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ERICA
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't know they take SAT's in China.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK
{DIALOGUE}: I wasn't talking about China anymore, I was talking about here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ERICA
{DIALOGUE}: You got 1600?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK
{DIALOGUE}: You can sing in an a Capella group.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 2.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRICA
{DIALOGUE}: Does that mean that you actually got nothing wrong?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK
{DIALOGUE}: Or you row crew or you invent a 25 dollar PC.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ERICA
{DIALOGUE}: Or you get into a final club.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARK
{DIALOGUE}: Or you get into a final club, exactly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ERICA
