{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE THAMES -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: we're looking at a stone bridge crossing a perfectly straight stretch of water against the backdrop of the medieval town of Henley, England--founded in 1179.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And after a moment of placid quiet--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ---BOOSHI
{DIALOGUE}: Two razor thin skulls explode out from under the bridge for the final, agonizing hundred-meter stretch of the ancient and prestigious Henley Royal Regatta.
{DIALOGUE}: The two boats are neck and neck coming out of the bridge.
{DIALOGUE}: The port-side boat is being crewed by the two Dutch members of the Ilollandia Roeiclub.
{DIALOGUE}: The starboard boat is being crewed by a pair of identical twins wearing tank tops bearing the "H" of Harvard.
{DIALOGUE}: We HEAR the ROAR come up from the CROWD in the viewing section.
{DIALOGUE}: The crowd is dressed as if for opening day at Ascot -- the women in flowing dresses and wide-brimmed hats, the men i n blazers and brightly colored floral ties.
{DIALOGUE}: But the young men in the boats can barely hear the crowd.
{DIALOGUE}: Just their own breathing as they pull against the longest natural.
{DIALOGUE}: straight stretch of water in the world--a mile and a half torture test against the best competition they've ever faced.
{DIALOGUE}: And they're neck and neck.
{DIALOGUE}: CAMERON and TYLER can't shake the Dutch.
{DIALOGUE}: The CROWD is going crazy in their own English way as none of them can remember ever seeing two boats this close this late.
{DIALOGUE}: Mixed in with the British crowd is a small contingent waving the flag of Holland and a slightly larger contingent of Americans.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 124.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We'll notice a stoic man in a VIP viewing section and latex we'll be introduced to him as Cameron and Tyler's father, Next to him is their mother, who can barely watch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Back on the boats it's just the breathing as the skulls slice through the water like jet-powered knives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 50 meters now and there's still no daylight between them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see a small trickle of blood from CAMERON's left hand begin to stream down his arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 25 meters and the Dutch and American fans are going crazy-- even the British aristocracy can't help but get caught ups the closest race in the history of the competition.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 'ATH_PT'ï¿½ is silently willing his boys one more fraction of boat speed-- the MOTHER has her hands over her mouth in praying position.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The blood that's covering CAMERON's left arm is being diluted by the sweat that's pouring down from his triceps as they dig, and pull, and pull, and pull, and---
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POP!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: --the finish gun is fired into the air, the oars come out of the water and the bodies of the crewmen slump over.
